Reading Racers.label: Reading Racers
Reading Racers.description: Reading Racers were a British motorcycle speedway team. Formed in 1968, they won four British League titles during their history. The club closed in October 2008 after the lease on Smallmead Stadium expired and the site was demolished. Wikipedia

PSŻ Poznań.label: PSŻ Poznań
PSŻ Poznań.description: Poznańskie Stowarzyszenie Żużlowe is a Polish speedway team based in Poznań who currently race in First League. The club never rode in the Polish top division. Their nickname is "The Scorpions". Wikipedia

Hackney Wick Wolves.label: Hackney Wick Wolves
Hackney Wick Wolves.description: Hackney Wick Wolves speedway opened in 1935 at Hackney Wick Stadium, Waterden Road, London, and operated until the outbreak of World War II in 1939. Wikipedia

ZKŻ Zielona Góra.label: ZKŻ Zielona Góra
ZKŻ Zielona Góra.description: Falubaz Zielona Góra is a Polish speedway team based in Zielona Góra who currently races in Speedway Ekstraliga. The club has won Polish Speedway League six times. It is commonly known as Falubaz due to one of its former names. Wikipedia

Włókniarz Częstochowa.label: Włókniarz Częstochowa
Włókniarz Częstochowa.description: Dospel CKM Włókniarz Częstochowa is a motorcycle speedway team based in Częstochowa, Poland. They were established in 1946. They compete in the Polish Ekstraliga. The club has won Polish Speedway League 4 times and European Club Cup 1 time in 2004. Wikipedia

Cradley Heath Heathens.label: Cradley Heathens
Cradley Heath Heathens.description: Cradley Heathens are a motorcycle speedway team from Dudley, England. The team was founded in 1945 and competed at the top level of British speedway until its closure in 1995. Wikipedia

Weymouth Wildcats.label: Weymouth Wildcats
Weymouth Wildcats.description: The Weymouth Wildcats were a British motorcycle speedway team based in Weymouth, England who raced in the National League. Wikipedia

Hackney Hawks.label: Hackney Hawks
Hackney Hawks.description: Hackney Hawks speedway opened in 1963 at Hackney Wick Stadium, Waterden Road, London and operated until 1983. Wikipedia

Scunthorpe Saints.label: Scunthorpe Scorpions
Scunthorpe Saints.description: The Scunthorpe Scorpions are a speedway team in the British Premier League. After three successful years in the Conference League the side were accepted into the Premier League for 2008. Wikipedia

Stal Gorzów Wielkopolski.label: Stal Gorzów Wielkopolski
Stal Gorzów Wielkopolski.description: Stal Gorzów Wielkopolski - polish speedway team based in Gorzów Wielkopolski who currently race in Speedway Ekstraliga. Wikipedia

GTŻ Grudziądz.label: GTŻ Grudziądz
GTŻ Grudziądz.description: Grudziądzki Klub Motocyklowy GKM S.A is a Polish motorcycle speedway team based in Grudziądz who currently race in First League. Wikipedia

Isle of Wight Islanders.label: Isle of Wight Islanders
Isle of Wight Islanders.description: The Isle of Wight Wightlink Islanders are a British speedway team. They currently compete in the National League and are holders of the National Trphy after winning it in June 2013, and ride their home meetings at the Smallbrook Stadium. Wikipedia

RKM Rybnik.label: RKM Rybnik
RKM Rybnik.description: Rybnicki Klub Motorowy is a Polish motorcycle speedway team based in Rybnik which currently competes in First League. Wikipedia

Southampton Saints.label: Southampton F.C.
Southampton Saints.description: Southampton Football Club is an English football club, nicknamed The Saints, based in the city of Southampton, Hampshire, who compete in the Premier League. Wikipedia
